# growthub-local — Agent Workflow

## Before any work
- Work in a worktree or feature branch, never directly on main.
- Branch must follow: `fix/`, `feat/`, `chore/`, `refactor/`, `docs/`, `ci/`, `test/`, `perf/`, `adapter/`, `sync/`
- Read source files before editing.

## Canonical runtime
Use **`scripts/runtime-control.sh`** from repo root: `up-main`, `up-branch <name>`, `up-pr <n>`, `stop`, `status`, `url`. Set `GH_SERVER_PORT` to match the API if it is not the script default; set `GH_LOCAL_ROOT` / `GH_CONFIG` when needed.

## Anti-patterns
- Do not improvise raw `pnpm --dir server` + `pnpm --dir ui` as the default path — use **`scripts/runtime-control.sh`**.
- Do not run **`worktree-bootstrap.mjs`** or manually sync into **growthub-core** unless a maintainer explicitly assigned that automation.

## Before pushing
Run `bash scripts/pr-ready.sh` — validates all pre-push contracts in one shot.

## Command guardrails
Run `bash scripts/guard.sh check-command "<command>"` before destructive git operations.

## Isolation
Use `growthub worktree:make` when you need a separate DB + port + instance.

## Version / grounding
Never cite semver from memory — see **`docs/ARTIFACT_VERSIONS.md`** and `cli/package.json` on your branch.

## Version bumps (only when source changes ship to npm)
- `cli/package.json` version +1
- `packages/create-growthub-local/package.json` version +1
- dep pin in create-growthub-local must match cli version exactly

## CI gates
- smoke, validate, verify — all 3 must pass
- `node scripts/release-check.mjs` must pass locally before merge
- After merge: run release.yml, confirm npm versions updated
